how to use funny to tell people the story
the difficult thing is finding moments of levity
"our giggle at the funeral" - there's got to be a moment when you say, "Oh
yeah, we're still celebrating life"
How do you keep the perspective of the show intact despite what is
happening?
He's not noticing the absence of the audience, he's just making a show.
He's surrounded by good people
the funniest human beings he's ever met in his life
The show is a conversation going on with the audience
as a comedian his eye is trained to see patterns - the inconsistencies make
you laugh
he said that "comedy =3D=3D tragedy + time"
Comedians place you in a world where things aren't completely real so you
can deal with what is real
