the thing I wish more americans would understand is that the two party
system lends itself to a situation where the american public will always be
at loggerheads
Americans aren't very good at being in a space where they're being honest
with themselves or the world
they prefer to be in a space of appeasement
unfortunately it may create peace in the short term - but doesn't create
understanding or conflict resolution in the long term
He tries to have the more uncomfortable conversations
this is the craziest time in human history
everyone is experiencing the same thing at the same time
He loves technology and has loved it his whole life
Pentium 386 - he thought it was a tv. it changed his life.
"The man who gave it to me said it was the future."
"What does that mean?"
"I don't know, but you're going to be the future so figure it out."
